    <h2>Scapehouse's Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We all have private issues in our lives that we would rather not share with other people. At Scapehouse, we respect that fact. Your privacy is important to us, and we will not violate the trust you place in us. That is why you can rest assured that your information is safe with us.</p>
    <p>Information you provide through this web site will not be abused, distributed, or sold, nor will any of your information be provided to third parties.</p>
    <p>You have full control of your information, and your information can be removed from our data banks at anytime upon your request.</p>
    <h3>Information Collection and Use</h3>
    <p><strong>Signup:&nbsp;</strong>Upon signing up for a Scapehouse account, we collect some information such as your name, email address, and a password. Some of this information, for example, your name and username, is listed publicly on Scapehouse, including on your profile page and in search results.</p>
    <p><strong>Additional Information:&nbsp;</strong>You may provide us with other details such as your sex, interests, and a profile picture. Some information such as your username and profile picture cannot be hidden from the public. However, you can choose to hide other details such as your work info.</p>
    <p><strong>Third Party Services:&nbsp;</strong>Scapehouse uses Google Analytics. Google Analytics helps us understand our visitors and how they use Scapehouse, and it collects information such as your IP address. This information is also sent to Google and their use of it is governed by their <a target="_blank" href="http://www.google.com/intl/en/privacy.html">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Cookies:&nbsp;</strong>Cookies are small pieces of textual information that are downloaded to your hard drive. They can be used to "remember" things for you, for example when you check the "Remember me" box before logging in.</p>
    <h3>Your Personal Information</h3>
    <p>You have complete control over your personal information and who gets to see it. If you wish, you can change these details or even remove them.</p>
    <p>We give you the tools you need to control how you share your information with other users (registered and/or non-registered) on Scapehouse.</p>
    <h3>How We Use Your Information</h3>
    <p>We may use your information to contact you regarding changes to our services. You may opt-out of non-essential communications.</p>
    <p>We may use your information to help manage and improve our services and to provide you with customer support.</p>
    <p><strong>Notifications:&nbsp;</strong>When YOU perform certain actions (such as commenting on another user's photo) on Scapehouse, other users may be notified of these actions. You CANNOT opt-out of these notifications. YOU may also be notified of certain actions performed by other users on Scapehouse (for example, if a user comments on one of your photos). You CAN opt-out of these notifications</p>
    <hr />
    <em>This Privacy Policy is subject to change. If we do make changes, we will notify you.</em>
